# If you have a pop-up in Arc GIS Online that has multiple categories and want to allow the viewer to select what they might be interested in, the following is code I use.
# To use this code, you need to select "Edit Text" in the pop-up, and then select the HTML editor, which also needs to be selected when you are done making edits. (Not to select the "OK" option--it won't let you anyway.)

<h2>
    Main Subject Heading
</h2>
<details>
    <summary><strong>Subheading Category 1</strong></summary> # The "strong" results in the subheading being bold, if desired. 
    <p>
        Descriptive text
    </p>
</details>
<details>
    <summary><strong>Subheading Category 2</strong></summary>
    <p>
        Descriptive text
    </p>
</details>
